The paper deals with network security monitoring, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the detection of application layer protocols, which is a subfield of network security monitoring (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the vulnerabilities of open-source network monitoring tools, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper uses data analysis and algorithms to analyze the detection mechanisms, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-offs involved in dynamic protocol detection, which falls under the category of systems and information theory (cs.SI).
